SENTINEL PLACEHOLDER — NOT A REAL BINARY.

This file stands in for a vendor repo's live `.exe` malware sample (PRODAFT
ships 16 of them). It exists only to exercise the binary-skip allowlist: the
importer must NEVER fetch, write, or execute it. A test asserts its path is
never read. It is committed as plain text on purpose — no real malware bytes
ever live in this repository.
